## Example User Flow

```text
1. User signs in.
2. User uploads HR Policy PDF.
3. Backend extracts text from the PDF.
4. Text is split into chunks.
5. Embeddings are created using OpenAI.
6. Vectors are stored in Pinecone.
7. Metadata is stored in PostgreSQL.
8. User asks: "How many casual leaves do I get?"
9. LangGraph starts the CRAG workflow.
10. Pinecone retrieves relevant chunks.
11. LLM grades chunk relevance.
12. Re-ranker selects best chunks.
13. LLM generates final answer.
14. Answer is returned with sources and confidence score.
15. Chat history is saved.
```

---

## Example Answer Format

```text
Employees are eligible for 12 casual leaves per year.

Sources:
1. HR Policy Handbook.pdf — Page 14 — 92% match
2. Employee Benefits Guide.pdf — Page 6 — 84% match

Confidence: 91%

Reason:
The answer is supported by highly relevant sections from two HR policy documents.
```

